The paper discusses the use of Restricted Boltzmann Machines (RBMs) for missing data inference tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of RBMs in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are related fields. Finally, the paper discusses the perception-distortion trade-off, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
